1
00:03:10,190 --> 00:03:11,565
Well, finally she's up!

2
00:03:16,362 --> 00:03:18,238
You're late, Natsuki.

3
00:03:19,908 --> 00:03:21,909
You could've woken me up, Mom!

4
00:03:22,452 --> 00:03:25,078
You said you could get up on your own.

5
00:03:33,630 --> 00:03:34,922
It's starting.

6
00:03:40,470 --> 00:03:41,929
Good morning, Amane.

7
00:03:42,931 --> 00:03:44,097
I win.

8
00:03:44,641 --> 00:03:46,016
Huh? In what?

9
00:03:46,517 --> 00:03:49,436
You said we'd see which of
us could get up earlier.

10
00:03:51,397 --> 00:03:53,440
Come on, focus on the exercise!

11
00:03:55,109 --> 00:03:56,526
You forgot, didn't you?

12
00:03:56,945 --> 00:03:58,445
No, it's not that...

13
00:03:59,280 --> 00:04:01,114
I simply didn't remember.

14
00:04:01,449 --> 00:04:02,532
Same thing!

15
00:04:04,035 --> 00:04:06,286
I'm... so... sorry!

16
00:04:17,674 --> 00:04:19,299
Good morning, Tama! How's it going?

17
00:04:21,678 --> 00:04:22,970
Oops... I'm sorry.

18
00:04:23,263 --> 00:04:24,596
Mom, look at this.

19
00:04:25,098 --> 00:04:27,557
See? Buy me a new one, please!

20
00:04:28,977 --> 00:04:30,602
Fix it yourself.

21
00:04:31,354 --> 00:04:33,480
What? That's impossible!

22
00:04:38,653 --> 00:04:40,821
Reading while you eat is bad manners.

23
00:04:41,990 --> 00:04:46,326
A businessman can't even take
time to enjoy his breakfast?

24
00:04:46,494 --> 00:04:48,662
I can't shake off the habit just yet.

25
00:04:51,916 --> 00:04:53,667
How was the field today?

26
00:04:54,502 --> 00:04:55,502
It got attacked.

27
00:04:55,878 --> 00:04:56,962
It's all messed up.

28
00:04:57,005 --> 00:04:58,797
Why don't you report it to the police?

29
00:04:58,840 --> 00:04:59,506
Yeah.

30
00:05:00,633 --> 00:05:03,135
I'll just catch them myself.

31
00:05:03,261 --> 00:05:06,013
<i>It's because grandpa's wasabi is too tasty.</i>

32
00:05:09,058 --> 00:05:12,686
"Miss Summer Vacation" will come to
the rescue in the worst-case scenario.

33
00:05:13,229 --> 00:05:14,313
Who is that?

34
00:05:14,939 --> 00:05:16,690
My alter ego.

35
00:05:17,859 --> 00:05:20,027
A mysterious superhero!

36
00:05:20,695 --> 00:05:21,945
Wasn't it supposed to be...

37
00:05:22,071 --> 00:05:23,363
- "Miss Summer Lady"?
- Thank you for the food!

38
00:05:23,489 --> 00:05:25,324
She must've transformed again.

39
00:05:25,408 --> 00:05:26,950
She's not a heroine anymore?

40
00:05:27,869 --> 00:05:29,870
Ah! It's so yummy!

41
00:05:30,330 --> 00:05:33,999
<i>It's now nine o'clock. Today's first game
of the Summer Baseball Championship...</i>

42
00:05:39,881 --> 00:05:41,298
You've got everything?

43
00:05:41,382 --> 00:05:42,049
Yup!

44
00:05:42,967 --> 00:05:43,633
Here!

45
00:05:45,636 --> 00:05:46,303
Thanks!

46
00:05:55,980 --> 00:05:56,897
Why?

47
00:05:57,774 --> 00:05:59,232
'Cause you'll be late.

48
00:05:59,567 --> 00:06:01,401
Go on, Natsuki. Thanks.

49
00:06:01,444 --> 00:06:02,903
Leave it to me!

50
00:06:03,571 --> 00:06:05,072
Hold on tight. I'll go fast!

51
00:06:06,616 --> 00:06:07,657
Hold on tighter!

52
00:06:08,201 --> 00:06:09,701
This is good enough.

53
00:06:14,415 --> 00:06:16,750
See you later!

54
00:06:16,793 --> 00:06:18,877
- Bye! - Be careful!

55
00:06:42,819 --> 00:06:44,027
I'm home!

56
00:06:44,237 --> 00:06:45,112
Welcome back!

57
00:06:45,738 --> 00:06:47,572
I'll have your lunch packed soon!

58
00:06:47,782 --> 00:06:50,409
Don't worry about it, Mom.
You worked the night shift.

59
00:06:50,952 --> 00:06:55,914
I won't be able to see you for a
week. This is the least I can do.

60
00:06:56,332 --> 00:06:58,625
Let me help you, then. I'll make rice balls.

61
00:07:00,711 --> 00:07:02,712
Kiyoshi, you've grown taller?

62
00:07:03,297 --> 00:07:04,297
No, I'm the same.

63
00:07:04,632 --> 00:07:08,718
- Bye! See you later! - Bye! See you later!

64
00:07:08,803 --> 00:07:09,719
Later!

65
00:07:10,221 --> 00:07:11,805
Give it your best!

66
00:07:11,848 --> 00:07:13,306
Bye-bye!

67
00:07:25,653 --> 00:07:29,114
COSMOS STORE

68
00:07:31,033 --> 00:07:33,577
Koji, what are those books for?

69
00:07:33,661 --> 00:07:35,662
I'm going to read them to my friends,

70
00:07:38,583 --> 00:07:40,250
'cause it gets boring there.

71
00:07:40,460 --> 00:07:42,419
Do you want to take my PlayStation?

72
00:07:42,587 --> 00:07:46,465
The goal is to cultivate friendship among us.

73
00:07:46,757 --> 00:07:49,468
We used to just camp out on a riverbed.

74
00:07:49,510 --> 00:07:51,845
I'd be worried about the little ones.

75
00:07:51,971 --> 00:07:53,847
There are only four in the entire school.

76
00:07:53,973 --> 00:07:55,098
Five.

77
00:07:55,391 --> 00:07:57,851
Amane's cousin, Natsuki,
has transferred to our school.

78
00:07:57,977 --> 00:08:00,187
Oh, yeah... What's she like?

79
00:08:00,438 --> 00:08:02,814
Well, she gets carried away easily.

80
00:08:03,232 --> 00:08:05,358
She let Pyon-Kichi out, after all.

81
00:08:10,239 --> 00:08:13,116
Mom's saying she's glad you're leaving!

82
00:08:13,409 --> 00:08:16,036
Here, Noriko. It's freshly squeezed.

83
00:08:16,245 --> 00:08:19,956
Hiroto, I've told you to wear pants outside.

84
00:08:20,041 --> 00:08:21,708
But the gate is over there!

85
00:08:24,420 --> 00:08:25,337
Well, I'm off.

86
00:08:25,963 --> 00:08:27,881
Shall I bring you something later?

87
00:08:27,965 --> 00:08:32,886
No. I'll send you an e-mail
if I need something. Besides,
Kiyoshi will look after us.

88
00:08:44,482 --> 00:08:46,483
Hey, Kiyoshi, what about tents?

89
00:08:46,901 --> 00:08:48,902
No, it's OK. We'll sleep in a classroom.

90
00:08:49,028 --> 00:08:49,986
Roger.

91
00:08:57,370 --> 00:08:58,078
Good morning.

92
00:08:58,120 --> 00:09:00,664
- Morning! - Morning!

93
00:09:01,207 --> 00:09:02,082
Morning.

94
00:09:02,708 --> 00:09:03,416
You're late!

95
00:09:03,543 --> 00:09:06,503
What? We're the last?

96
00:09:06,629 --> 00:09:07,754
- Yup. - Bingo!

97
00:09:08,089 --> 00:09:10,674
Gosh, I don't like it.

98
00:09:11,008 --> 00:09:13,093
It's not a race, you know.

99
00:09:13,302 --> 00:09:14,427
I know, but...

100
00:09:14,554 --> 00:09:16,763
Noriko, put this in the fridge, too.

101
00:09:16,889 --> 00:09:17,931
- Sure thing! - There!

102
00:09:22,270 --> 00:09:23,019
Let's see...

103
00:09:23,104 --> 00:09:25,272
PYON-KICHI'S HOUSE

104
00:09:25,565 --> 00:09:26,231
Huh?

105
00:09:32,446 --> 00:09:33,446
He's not back?

106
00:09:35,700 --> 00:09:36,700
Not yet.

107
00:09:48,296 --> 00:09:50,380
Are you still mad about Pyon-Kichi?

108
00:09:52,049 --> 00:09:53,592
I'm not mad, but...

109
00:09:53,634 --> 00:09:56,261
Well, I never dreamed that he'd run away.

110
00:09:57,638 --> 00:10:00,974
I'll buy you a new bunny. OK?

111
00:10:01,809 --> 00:10:02,475
No, thanks.

112
00:10:02,810 --> 00:10:03,310
What?

113
00:10:03,477 --> 00:10:04,477
Just... never mind!

114
00:10:12,194 --> 00:10:15,655
I'll be back a week from today at 6 PM.

115
00:10:15,740 --> 00:10:18,408
Oh, OK. Thank you.

116
00:10:18,951 --> 00:10:19,909
Take care.

117
00:10:20,286 --> 00:10:22,287
- Thanks. - Don't come to check on us!

118
00:10:22,913 --> 00:10:23,580
All right.

119
00:10:24,248 --> 00:10:27,167
We never came... last year
or the year before that.

120
00:10:27,501 --> 00:10:29,919
Because we trust Kiyoshi, after all.

121
00:10:41,182 --> 00:10:43,433
SUMMER CAMP

122
00:10:43,517 --> 00:10:46,186
LOOK AFTER YOURSELF ONE FOR ALL, ALL FOR ONE

123
00:10:50,691 --> 00:10:52,192
What are we gonna do now?

124
00:10:52,693 --> 00:10:55,445
Hey, wanna play a cell phone game?

125
00:10:55,780 --> 00:10:56,696
Some other time.

126
00:10:57,823 --> 00:10:59,699
We need to do our homework.

127
00:11:11,045 --> 00:11:12,337
But, it's still Day One.

128
00:11:12,546 --> 00:11:16,216
Why don't we go to the woods
and look for Pyon-Kichi?

129
00:11:18,219 --> 00:11:21,221
He may be homesick by now.

130
00:11:23,265 --> 00:11:33,692
Pyon-Kichi!

131
00:11:34,276 --> 00:11:35,735
Don't go so fast.

132
00:11:36,195 --> 00:11:37,987
You guys are slow.

133
00:11:38,656 --> 00:11:45,245
Pyon-Kichi!

134
00:11:48,332 --> 00:11:50,583
Be more serious!

135
00:11:50,751 --> 00:11:52,585
I am!

136
00:11:57,550 --> 00:12:00,927
How come Pyon-Kichi ran away to begin with?

137
00:12:01,178 --> 00:12:03,096
He was nice and calm.

138
00:12:06,434 --> 00:12:09,936
It was the last day of
school... right here...

139
00:12:13,941 --> 00:12:16,776
It's wide open and refreshing
out here, isn't it?

140
00:12:18,320 --> 00:12:20,447
You can play a little
before your crash course.

141
00:12:22,074 --> 00:12:23,950
I want you to learn to shake hands.

142
00:12:24,118 --> 00:12:25,952
The final goal is a back flip.

143
00:12:26,203 --> 00:12:28,621
Amane will be really impressed.

144
00:12:29,582 --> 00:12:30,749
Huh?

145
00:12:34,462 --> 00:12:35,420
What is it?

146
00:12:35,796 --> 00:12:38,715
You know. A hero needs a mascot.

147
00:12:38,966 --> 00:12:42,051
I was hoping I could train him to be one.

148
00:12:43,179 --> 00:12:44,971
You are an idiot.

149
00:12:45,306 --> 00:12:48,725
I hope he'll come back soon.

150
00:12:51,187 --> 00:12:52,103
Wanna drink?

151
00:13:08,496 --> 00:13:11,247
Koji, what's the matter?

152
00:13:11,624 --> 00:13:12,916
I fell down!

153
00:13:14,460 --> 00:13:16,419
Are you all right?

154
00:13:16,921 --> 00:13:18,254
I'm OK.

155
00:13:18,589 --> 00:13:20,340
I'm coming down!

156
00:13:38,192 --> 00:13:43,029
Mystery circles are created by a UFO
landing! This is a great discovery!

157
00:13:43,155 --> 00:13:44,113
UFO...

158
00:13:44,198 --> 00:13:44,864
Awesome!

159
00:13:47,034 --> 00:13:51,538
Aren't they supposed to be a
hoax? That's what I heard on TV.

160
00:13:51,831 --> 00:13:54,541
Who would play such a trick in our village?

161
00:13:54,917 --> 00:13:56,543
Hiroto might.

162
00:13:56,877 --> 00:13:59,212
He couldn't do anything this complicated.

163
00:13:59,255 --> 00:14:00,296
A locust!

164
00:14:00,381 --> 00:14:01,297
What? Where?

165
00:14:02,174 --> 00:14:04,717
I wonder if someone spilled
pesticide or something.

166
00:14:05,719 --> 00:14:09,556
Noriko, take a picture.
I'll put it up on our homepage.

167
00:14:09,890 --> 00:14:10,723
All right.

168
00:14:11,016 --> 00:14:14,561
Take a good one. This will change
the history of mankind.

169
00:14:14,770 --> 00:14:19,148
Don't pressure me.
I don't do well under pressure.

170
00:14:28,075 --> 00:14:29,075
Pyon-Kichi.

171
00:14:30,286 --> 00:14:31,244
Pyon-Kichi?

172
00:14:33,789 --> 00:14:34,581
Let's see...

173
00:14:34,915 --> 00:14:35,915
Pyon-Kichi?

174
00:14:39,086 --> 00:14:40,003
It's not him...

175
00:14:46,927 --> 00:14:48,344
Are you all right?

176
00:14:54,602 --> 00:14:56,019
Hey, is it a dog?

177
00:14:56,478 --> 00:14:57,854
What do we do?

178
00:14:58,314 --> 00:14:59,355
He's hurt.

179
00:15:00,316 --> 00:15:02,275
Noriko, give me your handkerchief.

180
00:15:12,786 --> 00:15:14,537
Koji, hit big!

181
00:15:14,663 --> 00:15:17,123
Kiyoshi, big bro! Clobber them!

182
00:15:24,423 --> 00:15:26,466
- Run! - Catch it! Catch it!

183
00:15:29,178 --> 00:15:30,470
Throw it at him!

184
00:15:30,971 --> 00:15:31,638
There!

185
00:15:32,806 --> 00:15:34,557
- OUT! - Good job!

186
00:15:36,018 --> 00:15:37,143
One more to go!

187
00:15:37,186 --> 00:15:38,478
That was close...

188
00:15:42,107 --> 00:15:45,151
Sorry, but I'm gonna hit a big one!

189
00:15:45,819 --> 00:15:47,987
Kiyoshi, big bro! Take her out!

190
00:15:48,113 --> 00:15:49,656
Take her out!

191
00:15:52,451 --> 00:15:53,993
All right!

192
00:16:09,301 --> 00:16:10,510
My home run...

193
00:16:10,678 --> 00:16:12,762
Look! He's all better!

194
00:16:17,643 --> 00:16:19,185
What a smart guy!

195
00:16:22,398 --> 00:16:23,856
First of all, let me say...

196
00:16:25,067 --> 00:16:27,360
Thank you. You saved my life.

197
00:16:33,033 --> 00:16:37,537
My name is Pochi. I'm from Planet
BOW in the Animal Stellar Region.

198
00:16:46,296 --> 00:16:48,715
You're a dog no matter how we look at you.

199
00:16:50,843 --> 00:16:53,052
I can't believe I'm being
lumped in with dogs!

200
00:16:55,014 --> 00:16:56,389
This is my ID.

201
00:16:56,515 --> 00:16:58,307
You really are an alien.

202
00:16:58,851 --> 00:17:00,351
Yes. Nice to meet you.

203
00:17:03,647 --> 00:17:05,064
Were they space alphabet letters?

204
00:17:06,108 --> 00:17:06,858
Yeah.

205
00:17:07,276 --> 00:17:09,027
How can you speak Japanese so well?

206
00:17:09,820 --> 00:17:14,240
I studied. I'm totally fine
with everyday conversation.

207
00:17:19,621 --> 00:17:20,830
His butt looks normal.

208
00:17:23,542 --> 00:17:25,877
Wh... Wh... What are you doing? How rude!

209
00:17:30,883 --> 00:17:33,926
So, Pochi, what have you
come to the Earth for?

210
00:17:35,888 --> 00:17:37,680
To study plants.

211
00:17:37,723 --> 00:17:39,348
Study plants?

212
00:17:39,725 --> 00:17:43,936
Yes, because I found a species that
went extinct 5 billion years ago.

213
00:17:44,855 --> 00:17:47,231
- Five billion years?
- Such an amazing thing exists?

214
00:17:47,858 --> 00:17:50,026
- Much older than the
Earth. - I have no clue.

215
00:17:50,903 --> 00:17:55,239
The flowers are called Zughaan,
and they are beautiful like you.

216
00:17:57,910 --> 00:18:02,622
18 years ago, microparticles believed to be
from Zughaan circulated in the underworld.

217
00:18:05,209 --> 00:18:07,210
I looked all throughout space.

218
00:18:08,045 --> 00:18:10,296
And, finally, I found them on this planet.

219
00:18:15,594 --> 00:18:18,971
Nothing from this undeveloped
planet can be taken out.

220
00:18:19,098 --> 00:18:22,433
So, I was doing my research
here, when they came.

221
00:18:22,518 --> 00:18:26,062
I fought back and kept the poachers away!

222
00:18:26,105 --> 00:18:28,397
But I got hurt.

223
00:18:32,194 --> 00:18:33,277
Are you all right?

224
00:18:35,030 --> 00:18:35,655
Yes!

225
00:18:38,575 --> 00:18:41,327
I've recovered, thanks to you.

226
00:18:48,043 --> 00:18:48,960
I'm glad.

227
00:18:50,462 --> 00:18:51,504
Breaking news!

228
00:18:52,548 --> 00:18:56,342
We're in the middle of experiencing
Close Encounters of the Third Kind.

229
00:18:56,760 --> 00:18:57,969
This is a major scoop!

230
00:18:58,053 --> 00:18:58,970
Yeah...

231
00:18:59,805 --> 00:19:02,014
Pochi, can I write an article on this?

232
00:19:02,266 --> 00:19:05,309
No. It's banned by an agreement.

233
00:19:05,435 --> 00:19:06,811
That sucks!

234
00:19:10,274 --> 00:19:11,482
Ah! She's come to.

235
00:19:14,236 --> 00:19:17,155
I scared you, didn't I? I apologize.

236
00:19:43,182 --> 00:19:43,848
Here.

237
00:19:44,183 --> 00:19:46,559
Do you think the poachers are coming back?

238
00:19:46,643 --> 00:19:47,685
Leave it to me.

239
00:19:48,020 --> 00:19:50,521
I'll have surveillance
beefed up once I get home.

240
00:19:52,149 --> 00:19:53,733
When are you coming back?

241
00:19:55,986 --> 00:19:58,196
I don't think we'll see each other again.

242
00:19:59,031 --> 00:20:00,072
What?

243
00:20:00,490 --> 00:20:02,658
We've only just met...

244
00:20:03,702 --> 00:20:08,164
Technically, I'm supposed to
avoid contact with you guys.

245
00:20:09,041 --> 00:20:12,335
I wanted to hear a lot more about space.

246
00:20:13,045 --> 00:20:14,045
I'm sorry.

247
00:20:17,716 --> 00:20:20,927
Well, I'd like to personally thank you.

248
00:20:24,014 --> 00:20:26,098
Do you have any wishes?

249
00:20:27,517 --> 00:20:29,268
Oh, yes! Pyon-Kichi!

250
00:20:31,521 --> 00:20:32,772
Find Pyon-Kichi for us!

251
00:20:33,232 --> 00:20:35,107
Is he one of you?

252
00:20:35,901 --> 00:20:36,734
- Yes! - No!

253
00:20:36,902 --> 00:20:41,739
He's a pet. A rabbit. He has ears this long.

254
00:20:44,201 --> 00:20:46,035
Sorry, but I can't.

255
00:20:46,536 --> 00:20:47,411
I see...

256
00:20:48,580 --> 00:20:53,626
Well, we can all look for
Pyon-Kichi together. Anything else?

257
00:20:55,712 --> 00:21:00,132
Oh! Please take Kiyoshi on a school trip!

258
00:21:00,425 --> 00:21:02,593
What? Me?

259
00:21:02,928 --> 00:21:06,806
Yeah, because they canceled
the trip starting this year!

260
00:21:06,890 --> 00:21:09,308
Three nights, four days to Kyoto and Nara.

261
00:21:10,018 --> 00:21:12,645
But there's no point if it's
just me and my teacher.

262
00:21:12,729 --> 00:21:14,397
Then, why don't we all go?

263
00:21:15,774 --> 00:21:17,066
I vote for that!

264
00:21:17,734 --> 00:21:21,279
Yeah! Let's go, Kiyoshi!

265
00:21:21,697 --> 00:21:23,656
Uh... sure.

266
00:21:24,116 --> 00:21:24,907
To where?

267
00:21:25,617 --> 00:21:27,493
As far as possible, then.

268
00:21:28,036 --> 00:21:29,829
All right. Got it.

269
00:21:31,248 --> 00:21:34,667
Then, I'll take you to the Moon,
the farthest mankind has traveled.

270
